This species can be recognized by the combination of the following features: 1) forewing with an additional short band between apical and pterostigmal bands (
Fig. 6
A–B); in males, 2) notal organ strongly arched dorsad at middle (
Fig. 6D
); 3) postnotal organ strongly raised and finger-like (
Fig. 6D
); 4) hypovalves distinctly reduced, shorter than one-fourth of hypandrium (
Fig. 6
E–F); 5) ventral aedeagal valves whitish with a pair of lateral hooks (
Fig. 6F, H
); and in females, 6) medigynium with broadly spatulate posterior arms, and a concealed axis (
Fig. 6L
).
